Minor suggestions (all optional, none blockers)

Multiple k-ring matches (edge case): If a sighting's k-ring overlaps two dwells, your current spec takes "any" match. I'd make build_dwell_lookup() / _get_dwell_center() pick the highest visit_count (i.e. lowest anomaly score) so you're never over-flagging on a borderline point. Super cheap to do with a quick max() in the ring check.
Hard-anomaly distance column (nice-to-have for v1.1): Adding distance_meters_to_nearest_dwell (even if just for hard anomalies) would give analysts instant context ("this is 450m from their nearest known spot"). Easy H3 distance calc during precompute.
Time decay (future v2): Old dwells from 2023 still count as "known territory" forever right now. If you ever want to age them out, we can add a simple exponential decay on visit_count based on last_seen—but totally out of scope for now.
